You MAY read, study, build, run, and reproduce Helix for ONE purpose: to VERIFY
for yourself that it is what it claims to be — that the from-raw trust chain
reproduces, that the tests and gates pass, and that the code hides nothing. You
may share verbatim copies for that same verification purpose.

You MAY NOT use Helix — in whole, in part, or its ideas — in any product,
service, or workload, commercial or not, without a separate written license from
the Licensor.

Third-party components vendored in this repository (the stage0 bootstrap tools
under stage0/M2-Planet/ and stage0/M2libc/, and the hex0/hex1/hex2/M0/M1/catm/
cc_amd64 rungs) keep their OWN upstream licenses — this license does not apply to
them. "Helix" is a trademark of the Licensor.

This is a SOURCE-AVAILABLE license. It is intentionally NOT an open-source
license: it grants the right to verify, not a general right to use.
